name: Bun Bo Hue
info: Bun bo hue is greatly admired for its balance of spicy, sour, salty and sweet flavors and the predominant flavor is that of lemon grass.

name: Bun Cha
info: Bun cha is from Hanoi which is capital of Viet Nam, a dish of Bun cha will have grilled pork, noodle, and a bowl of dipping sauce.

name: Bun Rieu
info: Bun rieu is one of famous noodle soup in Viet Nam. A bolw of bun rieu will have pork-based broth with tomatoes, onions, dried shrimp, and a crab paste/egg mixture as a topping.

name: Chinese Fried Rice
info: Fried rice is a dish of cooked rice that has been stir-fried in a wok or a frying pan and is usually mixed with other ingredients such as eggs, vegetables, seafood, or meat.

name: Peking Duck
info: Peking duck is a dish from Beijing (Peking) that has been prepared since the Imperial era. The meat is characterized by its thin, crispy skin, with authentic versions of the dish serving mostly the skin and little meat, sliced in front of the diners by the cook.

name: Kung Pao Chicken
info: Kung pao chicken is a popular Chinese restaurant dish of stir-fried chicken, peanuts and vegetables.

name: Wonton Soup
info: Wonton soup is a bouillon-like soup containing cooked, delicate wontons: dumplings filled with pork and/or shrimp mixed with some vegetables, soy sauce and sesame oil.

name: Spring Roll
info: Spring roll is a cylindrical casing of rice paper, or sometimes wheat-and-egg dough, filled with a shredded mixture of vegetables and often meat or seafood, served fresh or deep-fried.
